+## Retry And Blocking Rules
+
+The supervisor should classify repeated parser failures as a daemon-control problem, not as evidence that the domain task needs a larger rewrite.
+
+- One parser failure may be retried with a narrower prompt.
+- Two parser failures on the same domain task should block that domain task and append or select daemon-repair work.
+- A blocked domain task should not be revisited until the daemon has accepted syntax-preflight rollback and syntax-sensitive prompt diagnostics.
+- The next resumed domain proposal must be smaller than the failed proposal and must avoid package-wide exports or shared-contract rewrites unless the task explicitly requires them.
 
